  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>rice</strong> and 350ml [700ml] water to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/turmeric-chicken-curry/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and chop the <strong>onion[s] </strong>roughly</p><p>Peel and chop the <strong>garlic </strong>roughly</p><p>Peel the <strong>ginger</strong> (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and chop roughly (or grate)</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/turmeric-chicken-curry/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Split open the <strong>cardamom pods</strong>, removing the black inner seeds</p><p>Grind them slightly in a pestle and mortar, and heat a dry pan over a medium-low heat</p><p>Once warm, add the <strong>cardamom seeds</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>turmeric</strong></p><p>Toast the spices for 30 seconds, then add a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> to the pan</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/turmeric-chicken-curry/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>onion</strong>, <strong>ginger</strong>, <strong>garlic</strong> and<strong> lime leaves</strong> and continue to cook for 1 min</p><p>Add in the <strong>chicken</strong> <strong>stock mix</strong>,<strong> ground almonds</strong> and half [all] of the <strong>honey</strong> (you'll use the rest later)</p><p>Cook for a further 2 min</p><p>Transfer the mixture (keep the pan for step 6) to a processor and blitz until smooth paste - this is your curry paste</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/turmeric-chicken-curry/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut the <strong>chicken thighs</strong> into strips</p><p>Return the pan back to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p><strong>Once</strong> hot, add the chicken and cook for 2 min</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/turmeric-chicken-curry/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the curry paste to the chicken with 180ml [230ml] boiled water</p><p>Cover with a lid and cook on a medium-low heat for 10 min, then remove the lid and reduce for 5 min further until thickened to a good consistency</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/turmeric-chicken-curry/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, trim the <strong>green beans</strong></p><p>Add them to a pot with 200ml [<span class=\"text-danger\">250ml] </span>boiled water and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Cook for 7 min over a high heat or until they are tender</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/turmeric-chicken-curry/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the curry over the rice and green beans</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
